180
00:13:00,594 --> 00:13:02,630
Wha?!

181
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:04,962
H-He's dead?!

182
00:13:12,273 --> 00:13:14,434
Sorry for being late, Dad!

183
00:13:15,443 --> 00:13:16,944
Welcome back.

184
00:13:16,944 --> 00:13:18,112
Detective Kisaragi?!

185
00:13:18,112 --> 00:13:19,747
We figured out who your stalker is.

186
00:13:19,747 --> 00:13:20,614
Really?!

187
00:13:20,614 --> 00:13:23,981
Yeah, we're going to
go arrest him right now.

188
00:13:42,169 --> 00:13:47,742
"He asks her where her home is,
but she doesn't know"

189
00:13:47,742 --> 00:13:53,381
"He asks her what her name is,
but she doesn't know"

190
00:13:53,381 --> 00:13:59,019
"Meow, meow, meow-meow,
meow, meow, meow-meow"

191
00:13:59,019 --> 00:14:05,192
"All she does is cry,
the little kitty cat"

192
00:14:05,192 --> 00:14:11,732
"The policeman dog doesn't
know what to do and goes..."

193
00:14:11,732 --> 00:14:16,570
"Woof, woof, woof-woof,
woof, woof, woof-woof"

194
00:14:16,570 --> 00:14:17,738
Stop it!

195
00:14:17,738 --> 00:14:21,342
Don't yell. Please don't
scowl at me like that, Ryoko.

196
00:14:21,342 --> 00:14:24,745
You've got no right to
talk to me like you know me!

197
00:14:24,745 --> 00:14:26,680
What are you saying?

198
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,816
This is you and me.
We've even exchanged gifts.

199
00:14:28,816 --> 00:14:31,419
You're the one who just
kept sending them to me!

200
00:14:31,419 --> 00:14:34,989
Finding those flowers was tough, you know.

201
00:14:34,989 --> 00:14:39,493
If you hadn't been talking to
your friends and said you wanted them,

202
00:14:39,493 --> 00:14:41,395
I wouldn't have had to go to such trouble.

203
00:14:41,395 --> 00:14:42,563
What?

204
00:14:42,563 --> 00:14:47,368
And that doll, and those insects,
and that lovely dress...

205
00:14:47,368 --> 00:14:52,540
Oh, yes, and that dead hamster
I sent you on your birthday.

206
00:14:52,540 --> 00:14:53,874
What are you talking about?

207
00:14:53,874 --> 00:14:56,677
Love is about devoting yourself, isn't it?

208
00:14:56,677 --> 00:14:59,874
I really came to understand
that with this relationship.

209
00:15:02,817 --> 00:15:03,984
So why?

210
00:15:03,984 --> 00:15:05,853
I love you so much!

211
00:15:05,853 --> 00:15:08,022
What are you unhappy with?!

212
00:15:08,022 --> 00:15:11,058
No! Why?! Why are you doing this?!

213
00:15:11,058 --> 00:15:15,362
If it weren't for you, I wouldn't
have had to suffer like this!

214
00:15:15,362 --> 00:15:17,031
What did you say?

215
00:15:17,031 --> 00:15:18,399
What's there to suffer?!

216
00:15:18,399 --> 00:15:20,501
What part of my love is making you suffer?!

217
00:15:20,501 --> 00:15:22,203
Just stop it!

218
00:15:22,203 --> 00:15:26,674
Ryoko, what part of it
is making you suffer?!

219
00:15:26,674 --> 00:15:29,973
...you, too, will go to Hell.

220
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:34,982
I'm going to ask you one last time, Ryoko.

221
00:15:34,982 --> 00:15:38,452
What part of me is making you suffer?!
Well?! What is it?!

222
00:15:38,452 --> 00:15:41,422
-Answer me, Ryoko!
-Nooo!

223
00:15:41,422 --> 00:15:42,823
...to Hell.

224
00:15:42,823 --> 00:15:44,723
Ryoko!

225
00:15:48,496 --> 00:15:52,867
Your grievance has been heard.

226
00:15:52,867 --> 00:15:54,664
Hey, what are you doing in there?!

227
00:15:57,137 --> 00:15:58,604
Hey, hold it!

228
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:02,776
It's gone! The doll's gone?!

229
00:16:02,776 --> 00:16:04,710
Are you all right, Ryoko?

230
00:16:06,313 --> 00:16:09,149
The covenant has been established.

231
00:16:09,149 --> 00:16:11,117
Look down at your chest.

232
00:16:15,656 --> 00:16:17,715
It's the seal of the covenant.

233
00:16:19,493 --> 00:16:22,485
The seal...of the covenant?

234
00:16:55,162 --> 00:16:58,529
Ai, I'll leave your under-kimono here.

235
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,730
Thank you, Grandma.

236
00:17:54,121 --> 00:17:55,679
Dad...

237
00:17:59,493 --> 00:18:02,963
I won't forgive you. You betrayed me.

238
00:18:02,963 --> 00:18:04,658
I'll make you regret it!

239
00:18:09,603 --> 00:18:10,831
Welcome.

240
00:18:16,110 --> 00:18:18,874
Damn! Lights-out time, huh?

241
00:18:26,854 --> 00:18:28,082
Wha?!

242
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,033
Is something the matter?

243
00:18:45,039 --> 00:18:47,541
Oh, you can't do this with the water.

244
00:18:47,541 --> 00:18:50,066
You shouldn't leave it running.

245
00:18:57,317 --> 00:19:00,377
"Youji Takamura"

246
00:19:04,191 --> 00:19:07,183
Wh-Wh-What's going on?!

247
00:19:08,829 --> 00:19:09,963
I'm so sorry.

248
00:19:09,963 --> 00:19:13,100
-Dad!
-Dear!

249
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,568
No! Dear!

250
00:19:34,688 --> 00:19:36,123
So he's dead.

251
00:19:36,123 --> 00:19:38,358
Serves him right.

252
00:19:38,358 --> 00:19:42,796
I'll send you right after
your father, Ryoko.

253
00:19:42,796 --> 00:19:44,696
It's what you get for betraying me.

254
00:19:50,304 --> 00:19:52,005
Bastard!

255
00:19:52,005 --> 00:19:56,704
How dare you make my daughter
suffer like that?!

256
00:19:58,779 --> 00:20:02,306
Why you! Take that! And that!

257
00:20:08,155 --> 00:20:11,625
Well? Has it gotten
through to you a little?

258
00:20:11,625 --> 00:20:15,462
She means, do you feel like
repenting for what you did?

259
00:20:15,462 --> 00:20:16,864
Captain Kisaragi.

260
00:20:16,864 --> 00:20:18,832
Wh-What are you talking about?

261
00:20:18,832 --> 00:20:20,968
I haven't done anything wrong.

262
00:20:20,968 --> 00:20:22,636
Oh-ho, is that so?

263
00:20:22,636 --> 00:20:24,304
It's Ryoko's fault!

264
00:20:24,304 --> 00:20:26,073
It's her fault for betraying me!

265
00:20:26,073 --> 00:20:28,976
It's all her fault!

266
00:20:28,976 --> 00:20:31,069
Hear that, Miss?

267
00:20:40,354 --> 00:20:43,757
O pitiful shadow lost in the darkness...

268
00:20:43,757 --> 00:20:46,593
Demeaning and bringing harm to others...

269
00:20:46,593 --> 00:20:49,221
A damned soul, wallowing in sin...

270
00:20:50,564 --> 00:20:53,362
Care to give death a try?

271
00:21:10,918 --> 00:21:14,012
Wh-Wh-Where am I?

272
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:24,565
W-Wait! Where are we going?!
Wh-Where in the world are we?!

273
00:21:24,565 --> 00:21:27,401
Where are we, I wonder? Eh, Mister?

274
00:21:27,401 --> 00:21:29,837
Wh-What are you doing?! Let me go!

275
00:21:29,837 --> 00:21:32,397
No can do.

276
00:21:50,357 --> 00:21:54,428
I consign this grievance to Hell...

277
00:21:54,428 --> 00:21:59,566
"Little lost, little lost kitty cat"

278
00:21:59,566 --> 00:22:04,469
"Where is your home?"

279
00:22:07,741 --> 00:22:08,976
